        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 25 at 4:49PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 449 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Cooley, or 19 miles north of Ruston, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Farmerville, Bayou D Arbonne Lake and Shiloh.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
